4:
*pant* Mind going for that finishing
blow now?
15: Damn it! They got away AGAIN!
19: Oh... Did we... mess this up?
23:
Nah, not at all. Those guys are
tough, so actually, I'd say you saved
our skins. Thanks for that.
27:
Yeah, that was the closest we've
come to beating them! You guys're
pretty strong!
31:
By the way... What is this place? You
guys don't seem like you're from the
Phantagrande Skydom.
36:
About that... Please listen carefully
and calmly...
41:
...So we got sucked into a "shift" and
ended up in another world.
45:
Those primal beasts that followed
you... They're too dangerous to be
left alone.
48:
Is there anything we should know
before the next time we deal with
them?
52:
Guess we should start from the top.
We're part of the Society, and it's our
job to hunt those primal beasts
down.
61:
Oh, come on! You can't expect me
to keep everything secret in a
situation like this!
65:
That doesn't mean you should share
EVERYTHING!
69:
Ugh, fine. We're in another world
anyways, right?
74:
I see... So primal beasts are godlike
beings, and the specific ones you're
dealing with possess the ability to
read memories and alter their forms
and abilities based on them.
78:
Yeah, Zeta fought the originals a
while back. Good thing for us is that
these copies aren't as strong as the
real deal.
83:
I don't want to even think about the
havoc they can wreak in another
world... We've got to deal with them
sooner than later.
88:
I think I get the gist of it... In other
words, it's time to put the
Kaleidoscope on lockdown!
93:
Hiring some skilled adventurers to
help us track down the beasts might
be a good idea.
98:
We'll definitely have to let them
know their targets can change
shape. We've gotta catch them
before they escape the
Kaleidoscope...
104: Wow, you guys took all that in stride.
109:
Eh, you get used to this kind of stuff
around here.
119:
Now I'm itching to get going! Zeta,
let's do a sweep of the Kaleidoscope—
123:
Nope! We're staying put! No rash
actions when we don't have our
usual resources at our disposal.
126:
Listen, everyone, I appreciate all the
help. But don't go thinking you'll be
able to defeat the primal beasts on
your own.
131: You saying we're not strong enough?
136:
Ah, no, nothing like that. It's just that
regular weapons and magic aren't
enough to beat them.
139:
You're going to need strategy and...
well, mostly special weapons. Like
mine.
144:
Bea and I are the only ones that can
deal the final blow.
149:
Yeah, you can count on me! I'll get
them next time for sure!
154:
Bea... If charging in alone worked
every time, we wouldn't be here right
now.
159:
We had them cornered though,
didn't we? Our next attempt should
go smoother...
163:
That's the thing. Landing the final
blow is always rough since they're
good at running away. If only we
had another friend from back home
here...
168: What if you returned home first?
172:
The entrance that brought you here
is still open. Probably.
181:
Now that you mention it, the hole we
fell through was still open when we
left. Which means... We could punch
our primal pals back through it.
187:
Is that all? I could do that in my
sleep!
192:
We should hurry then. There's no
telling when that hole will close.
198:
Let's get this show on the road!
Prepare to witness Palpebra's
adventurers doing what they do
best!
202: Should we wait here for now?
207:
There are a few more details I'd like
to iron out. Would you mind joining
us at our home base?
212:
It's a special sort of place, so you'll
have to keep its location a secret.
223:
Can you blame us? Today was
crazy, and then you brought us to
an awesome place like this.
226:
Couldn't help but mull over our
thoughts, wondering about other
worlds... and our world's place in this
sky...
230:
Plus dinner was awesome! Alk,
you're pretty good in the kitchen!
234:
We owe you a lot. Seriously. Thanks
for everything.
239:
I-it's the least we can do since the
battle plan hinges on you both more
than us...
245:
Don't you worry about a thing! Once
we kick those primal beasts back
home, we'll rally our crew friends
and take them down!
248:
...You know, now that I think about it,
you guys remind me an awful lot of
that crew.
257:
They're a mixed bunch, 
but... they're all good people.
261:
If they were in your position, they
would've helped us out without a
doubt—just like you're doing!
266: I'd love to meet them one day.
270:
Hehe, you guys would get along like
a house on fire!
275:
For sure. Who knows? Might even
actually happen one day, given their
penchant for the unexpected.
281: There it is! That has to be it!
285:
Thanks for the tip. You adventurers
over here are pretty capable after
all.
300:
Heheh, guess we'll just have to beat
you through after all!
305: Works for me! Let's go, Bea!
